# deep-reasoning M1 (docs/plans/deep-reasoning.md §4bis): PROVENANCE. Every fact the
# comprehension parser EXTRACTS keeps the raw source fragment it came from, as
# fact_source(FactRepr, Concept, "raw"). This is the prerequisite for self-correction
# (M4): the deep-reasoning loop can return to a suspect fact's source and re-check it.
# Hermetic base -> every fact is genuinely learned, and its source genuinely recorded.

# Extract a locative fact -> it is stored WITH its source fragment.
> France is located in Western Europe
< Learned: located_in(france, western_europe).
# ...and the source is queryable by concept.
> where did you learn about France?
< I learned located_in(france, western_europe) from: "france is located in western europe".

# A membership fact carries provenance too.
> A whale is a mammal
< Learned: mammal(whale).
> what is your source for whale?
< I learned mammal(whale) from: "a whale is a mammal".

# Honest: a concept with no recorded extraction has no source (never invented).
> where did you learn about Mars?
< I don't have a recorded source for mars.
